info.headline: Wind Advisory issued December 26 at 3:02PM PST until December 26 at 7:00PM PST by NWS Seattle
info.description: ...WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 7 PM PST THIS EVENING... ...WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 11 PM THIS EVENING TO 1 AM PST WEDNESDAY... * WHAT...For the first Wind Advisory, southeast winds 10 to 15 mph. For the second Wind Advisory, southwest winds 35 to 45 mph with gusts up to 65 mph expected. * WHERE...North Coast and Central Coast. * WHEN...For the first Wind Advisory, until 7 PM PST this evening. For the second Wind Advisory, from 11 PM this evening to 1 AM PST Wednesday. * IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects. Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may result. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Recent heavy rains lead to increased risk for trees to blow over with reduced root stability.
info.instruction: Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.
